      <p class="mt-xxlg">
      Currently, many do it yourself (DIY) projects are failing unnecessarily due to a lack or knowledge sharing and community. To solve this problem, we created Dittly, a platform on which users can plan projects by saving milestones, lists, materials, and estimates, and then track and share their project progress with the home-improvement community.</p>
      <p>To address the needs of your target audience, Dittly will be available on smartphone, tablet, and desktop computer, and will feature a simple, very easy to use intrface, and an experience designed to be intuitive, deligtful, and most of all, helpful.</p>
      <p>To ensure our product, build, and deployment is flawless, our tech stack consists of Docker, Node.js, Next.js, and React.js. </p>
      <p>Our current team consists of myself and Mike Nikles.</p>
